pr.body:
Homepage calendar was hardcoded to May 2026 and the sermon generation prompt had no scripture references, letting the model invent Bible verses unrelated to the actual liturgical day.

## Changes

### Homepage – dynamic calendar month
- Replaced module-level `const may2026 = getMonthData(2026, 5)` with a runtime computation inside the async component, derived from `publicationDate`
- Month heading `Mai 2026` and the hardcoded week-label fallback `KW ${18 + index}/2026` are now computed from the current publication year/month

```ts
// before
const may2026 = getMonthData(2026, 5);        // frozen at build time
// <h2>Mai 2026</h2>                           // hardcoded
// KW ${18 + index}/2026                       // hardcoded fallback

// after (inside async component)
const [pubYear, pubMonth] = publicationDate.split('-').map(Number);
const currentMonthData = getMonthData(pubYear, pubMonth);
```

### Homepage – dynamic sermon loading + `force-dynamic`
- Replaced static `import dailySermon from '…/daily-sermon.json'` with a runtime `loadCurrentSermon()` call so the page immediately reflects the sermon CI commits to `main` without a redeploy
- Added `export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'`; static import kept as fallback

### Sermon generation – liturgically grounded prompt
- Imports `getLiturgicalReadings(date)` and injects the day's assigned Lesung / Psalm / Evangelium into the prompt
- System message now explicitly instructs the model to use only the provided references (e.g. Pfingstsonntag → Apg 2,1-11 · Ps 104 · Joh 20,19-23) and not invent others
